            <abstract>
                <p>This document provides a description of the church and a precise count of its measurements and parts (size of the enclosure, search for the foundations, height, width and length of the church, number of columns, windows, doors and various architectural elements). He also mentions adjacent buildings (four churches, a house of stewardship, a common room, a chapel that is perhaps the one housing the Ark). This report ends with the dates of the construction of the church, which began in the year 49 of Mercy and was completed in the year 91, accompanied by a reflection on entropy. <date notAfter="1538" type="production">Not after 1538</date></p>
